  "prompt": "Can I deposit cash without cheque in SBI?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deposit cash in State Bank of India (SBI) without a cheque using several methods:\n\n1. Cash Deposit at Branch Counter\n- Visit any SBI branch\n- Fill cash deposit slip\n- Provide your account details\n- Submit cash and slip to the teller\n\n2. Cash Deposit Machines (CDMs)\n- Available at many SBI branches\n- Insert your ATM/debit card\n- Select deposit option\n- Insert cash\n- Receive transaction receipt\n\n3. Cash Deposit through Cardless Deposit Slip\n- Fill deposit slip with account details\n- Deposit cash at branch counter\n- No need for bank card\n\n4. Cash Deposit through Digital Banking\n- Use SBI YONO app or internet banking\n- Find nearest branch or CDM\n- Follow deposit instructions\n\nImportant points:\n- Carry valid ID proof\n- Ensure account number is correct\n- Keep transaction receipt\n- Some limits may apply for cash deposits\n- Minor restrictions might exist for non-account holders\n\nNote: Specific procedures might vary slightly, so it's recommended to confirm exact process with your local SBI branch.",
